in English history, from thelast years of Edward III [1376-77] to the premature death of Henry V [1422]. Walsingham describes the many dramas of this period in vivid detail, including the Peasants' Revolt [1381], the deposition and murder of Richard II [1399-1400], The Welsh revolt of Owain Glyn Dwr [1403] and Henry V's victory at Agincourt [1415]; they are brought to life here in this new translation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aHistory of Religion. 4aMedieval History. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Personal Memoirs.2bisacsh  aAdministrative Records.  aChronicles.  aEnglish History.  aHistorical Events.  aLiterary Works.  aMedieval Chronicle.  aPolitical Machinations.  aThomas Walsingham.1 aClark, James G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPreest, David G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPreest, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013z978311143139040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978184615380840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781846153808423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781846153808/original  a978-3-11-143139-0  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013b2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles